column14: RFT NOTE: MANY PANELS SHOULD HAVE BEEN DOUBLE SHOTS (GREATER THAN 0.75M DEPTH) BUT THEY WEREN'T, AND NO REASON WAS GIVEN IN THE EHSN. TECH NOTE:  FOR CABLEWAY MEASUREMENTS WHERE THE WEIGHT IS ABOUT 0.3m BELOW THE CUPS,  YOU DO NOT HAVE TO DO .2/.8 UNLESS DEPTHS ARE GREATER THEN 1.5m.  THIS IS STANDARD PROCEDURE IS DOES NOT HAVE TO BE NOTED. HFC Comments: Control Condition: CLERMeasurement Section Codition: ClearWeather Condition: Ovecast Reset HG and HG2 for 1125 pst. Reset a few more times but it never held. The river is surging quite heavily at area of sensors. At 1230 pst I set Burst averaging to 6x 5s samples in 30 seconds. Then reset again @1231. Burst averaging was not on prior. Reset at 1235 looks good! Mid-section
